The paper deals with private information retrieval (PIR), which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of multiple servers and side information suggests that the paper may also be relevant to distributed systems (cs.DS) and parallel computing (cs.CC). Finally, the concept of virtual side information introduces a new theoretical framework, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of signal processing and machine learning (cs.SI).
